
== Tutorial: Test Eclipse 3.x RCP applications

=== Create project
		
			Create a new
			Eclipse RCP
			application called
			_de.vogella.swtbot.app_
			based on the "Eclipse
			application
			with a
			view"
			template.
		
		
			Change the class View to the following.
		
		
			<programlisting language="java">
				<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
					parse="text" href="./examples/first/View.java[]
----
		
		
			This
			view
			defines two text fields, one of them will be identified by SWTBot
			via the
			label and the other through an SWTBot specific ID.
		
	

=== Create test plug-in
		
			Create another
			Eclipse plug-in called
			_de.vogella.swtbot.tests_
			.
		
		
			Add the following dependencies  to the
			_MANIFEST.MF_
			file for your test project.

			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					org.eclipse.ui
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					org.junit4
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					org.hamcrest
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					org.eclipse.swtbot.swt.finder
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					org.eclipse.swtbot.eclipse.finder
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		
		
			Create the following class which defines the JUnit test.
		

		
			<programlisting language="java">
				<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
					parse="text" href="./examples/first/UserInterfaceTester1.java[]
----
		
		
			Right-click on the test and select
			menu:Run As [SWTBot Test]
			. In the
			launch configuration maintain your application and add the
			_de.vogella.swtbot.tests_ and _de.vogella.swtbot.app_
			plugins
			as well as
			their
			dependencies to the launch configuration.
		

		
